Sentencas: The reaction kinetics and mechanisms between 8 mol % yttriastabilized zirconia (YSZ) and 30 mol% Sr-doped lanthanum manganite (La0.65Sr0.30MnO3, LSM) with A-site deficiency for the application of planar solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) were investigated.
Titulo: Reaction kinetics and mechanisms between La0.65Sr0.3MnO3 and 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia

Sentencas: The LSM/YSZ green tapes were cofired from 1200 to 1400 degreesC for 1 to 48 h and then annealed at 1000 degreesC for up to 1000 h.
Titulo: Reaction kinetics and mechanisms between La0.65Sr0.3MnO3 and 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia

Sentencas: The results showed that the diffusion of manganese cations first caused the amorphization of YSZ, and then the formation of small La2Zr2O7 (LZ) or SrZrO3 (SZ) crystals if treated for a longer time at 1400 degreesC. The ambipolar diffusion of the Mn-O pair, transported through the migration of oxygen vacancy, plays an important role in the formation of secondary phases.
Titulo: Reaction kinetics and mechanisms between La0.65Sr0.3MnO3 and 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia

Sentencas: The diffusion of LSM to YSZ and substitution of Mn for Zr both result in the enhanced concentration of oxygen vacancy, leading to the formation of a void-free zone (VFZ).
Titulo: Reaction kinetics and mechanisms between La0.65Sr0.3MnO3 and 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia

Sentencas: No additional reaction products in annealed LSM/YSZ specimens, treated at 1000 degreesC for 1000 h, were detected.
Titulo: Reaction kinetics and mechanisms between La0.65Sr0.3MnO3 and 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia

Sentencas: The interfacial reactions, detailed reaction kinetics, and mechanisms are reported.
Titulo: Reaction kinetics and mechanisms between La0.65Sr0.3MnO3 and 8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia
